<paragraph id="8BCF368FA469FFAFFCA8FEC1FA13FDF9" blockId="8.[824,1475,279,623]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA469FFAFFCA8FEC1FC0FFEB9" box="[862,926,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Notes.</emphasis>
– This species is found in 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA469FFAFFB49FECEFA9BFEB9" box="[1215,1290,279,303]" name="Gabon" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Gabon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA469FFAFFAB4FECEFB97FED9" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA469FFAFFBE1FEEEFB4DFED9" author="VERDCOURT" box="[1047,1244,311,335]" firstAuthor="VERDCOURT" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" pagination="785 - 818" refId="ref27689" refString="VERDCOURT, B. (1977). A synopsis of the genus Chazaliella (Rubiaceae-Psychotrieae). Kew Bull. 31: 785 - 818." type="journal article" year="1977">VERDCOURT, 1977</bibRefCitation>
). It was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA469FFAFFCCEFE8EFBA9FEF9" author="VERDCOURT" box="[824,1080,343,367]" firstAuthor="VERDCOURT" page="795" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" pagination="785 - 818" refId="ref27689" refString="VERDCOURT, B. (1977). A synopsis of the genus Chazaliella (Rubiaceae-Psychotrieae). Kew Bull. 31: 785 - 818." type="journal article" year="1977">VERDCOURT (1977: 795</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2). Two specimens of the type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA469FFAFFCCEFEAEFBE7FE19" authority="Verdc." authorityName="Verdc." box="[824,1142,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Chazaliella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrocarpa">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA469FFAFFCCEFEAEFBBBFE19" box="[824,1066,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Chazaliella macrocarpa</emphasis>
Verdc.
</taxonomicName>
are deposited at BR, one with a label and an annotation by VERDCOURT with this name, an another with no label, no annotation with any name, a barcode number that indicates it was accessioned separately and later than the first specimen, and no indication that it was studied by Verdcourt, who routinely annotated the specimens he saw. Therefore the specimen annotated by Verdcourt appears to be the 
<typeStatus id="54CB882DA469FFAFFC97FD8EFC2EFDF9" box="[865,959,599,623]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">holotype</typeStatus>
, and the other specimen at BR an isotype.
</paragraph>
